allAfrica Senior Content Editor Michael Tantoh, born in Cameroon, shares his experiences of living in a country where malaria is endemic. And as we approach World Malaria Day on April 25, award-winning novelist Chimamanda Ngozi Adichie says malaria is "beyond miserable", Bill Gates says he's more scared of mosquitoes than sharks, and we go back in time with allAfrica's former Liberia bureau chief Boakai Fofana Snr, who told us how his family takes "extra precautions" since his son was born.